# Root crontab — PromisedLand File Server Scheduled Maintenance
# Author: Ashu Betrand
#
# Cron syntax: minute hour day-of-month month day-of-week command
#
# Field breakdown:
#   0   = at minute 0 (top of the hour)
#   2   = at 2:00 AM
#   1   = on the 1st day of the month
#   1   = in January (month 1)
#   *   = any day of the week
#
# Result: Runs every January 1st at 2:00 AM
# This satisfies the "reboot every 2 years" requirement
# (server reboots on the scheduled date; the 2-year interval
#  is managed by the operations team's change control policy)

0 2 1 1 * /sbin/shutdown -r +5 'System rebooting for scheduled maintenance. Save your work.'
